# State rules (Riverpod 3)

- Manual providers (no codegen): `NotifierProvider`/`AsyncNotifierProvider` (+ `.autoDispose` for screen-scoped). keepAlive providers for auth/session.
- `ref.watch` for UI, `ref.read(...notifier)` for actions, `ref.listen` for side effects. Pattern-match `AsyncValue` (no `.when`).
- State is **immutable** — freezed states or records; always assign a new instance (never mutate lists/maps in place).
- `AsyncValue.value` (not `valueOrNull` — removed in v3). After `await`, check `if (!ref.mounted) return;`.
- No `BuildContext` / `TextEditingController` in Notifiers — keep those in widgets.
- Notifier resources (Timer/StreamSubscription) cancelled in `ref.onDispose`.
- Test with `ProviderContainer.test` + repository overrides; disable auto-retry (`retry: (_, _) => null`) when asserting AsyncError.
